label: High blood pressure or hypertension (except that occurred during pregnancy and did not last after pregnancy)?
Coronary artery disease (blockages in your heart vessels) or angina (chest pain)?
Stroke or TIA (Transient Ischemic Attack or Mini-Stroke)?
COPD (emphysema, chronic bronchitis, obstructive pulmonary disease)?
Asthma, to the point that you use inhalers daily or have been to the hospital for your asthma?
Cancer (including leukemia or lymphoma) undergoing active treatment?
Anemia or other blood disorder (do not include leukemia or lymphoma)?
